Date: Friday 6 September 2002 10:04:50 +0200 X-Mailer: Microsoft Outlook Express 5.00.2919.6900DM MIME version: 1.0 Content type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii" Content transfer encoding: 8bit -To: ilug-admin@linux.ie X-Mailman-Version: 1.1 Precedence: Bulk List ID: Irish Linux User Group X-Beenthere: ilug@linux.ie APPLICATION FOR URGENT BUSINESS ASSISTANCE ------------------------ -------------------- --------- Your contact information was provided to me by the Chamber of Commerce. It was given to me due to my diplomatic status, as I did not disclose the actual reasons why I sought contact. But I have been assured that you are reputable and trusted to be helpful.  My name is Laurent Mpeti Kabila (Jnr) and I am the second son of the late President LAURENT DESIRE KABILA, immediate past president of the DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF THE CONGO in Africa, who was assassinated by his opposition by his personal bodyguards in his bedroom on Tuesday, January 16, 2001. the privilege of receiving a mandate from my father, colleagues to request your immediate and urgent cooperation in order to receive into your bank account the sum of US$25 million (twenty-five million dollars) and several thousand carats of diamond.  This money and treasure was deposited in the vaults of a security company in Europe and South Africa.  SOURCES OF DIAMONDS AND FUNDS In August 2000, my father, as defense minister and president, met with his cabinet and army chief regarding the 2000-2001 defense budget, which was $700 million. so he directed one of his best friends. Frederic Kibasa Maliba, who was Minister of Mines and leader of the political party known as Union Sacree de I Radical Opposition and Ses Allies (USORAL), to purchase weapons for $200 million on January 5, 2001; to complete an arms deal, my father was murdered. f.K. Maliba (FKM) and I decided to keep the money with a foreigner who would then use it to run in political elections. Nevertheless, we have decided to introduce you or your company to a company that will pay the above amount and diamonds to the account you indicate. This transaction should be completed within seven (7) business days, and as part of your cooperation and partnership, we have unanimously agreed that you will be entitled to 5.5% of the money once you successfully receive it in your account. The nature of your company is irrelevant to the successful completion of this transaction. We require your complete cooperation and commitment to ensure a 100% risk-free transaction on both sides and to protect those involved in this transaction, strict confidentiality and the highest quality. secrecy is required even after the successful completion of this transaction. If this proposal is acceptable to you, I kindly request you to provide me with your personal telephone and fax via my e-mail box in order to initiate the transaction immediately.  All correspondence is directed to my counsel: Joseph Edward. I count on your honor that you will keep my secret SECRET. I am waiting for an urgent reply. Thanks. Best regards, MPETI L. Date: Fri 6 Sep 2002 10:28:15 +0100 X-Mailer: Microsoft Outlook Express 5.00.2919.6900DM MIME Version: 1.0 Content Type: Text/Plain; charset="us-ascii" Message ID: Content Transfer Encoding: 8-bit automatic X-MIME conversion: quote-print to 8-bit via lugh.tuatha.org id KAA04073 Subject: [ILUG] From the desk of: George Osawy From: ilug-admin@linux.ie Errors-To: ilug-admin@linux.ie X-Mailman Version: 1.1 Precedence: Collective List ID: Irish Linux User Group X-Beenthere: ilug@linux.ie NIGERIA ELECTIRC OFFICE OF ENERGY FEDERAL SECRETARIAT IKOYI-LAGOS.  FROM THE DESK: George Osawa I am the chairman of the National Electricity Authority (NEPA) Contract Review Committee.  Although this suggestion may come as a surprise to you as it comes from someone you don't know or have never seen before, but after careful deliberation with my colleagues, I have decided to contact you based on Intuition.   We are asking for your humble and confidential help in taking custody of seventy-one million five hundred thousand US dollars.{USD 71,500,000.00}. This amount ($71.5 million) represents the invoice contract amount currently held in the Central Bank of Nigeria's offshore payment account as an unclaimed contract entitlement which can be easily withdrawn or drawn up or paid to any beneficiary recommended by my committee.  In this notice, you will be presented to NEPA as a contractor who performed a contract for the above amount and did not receive payment.  Proposed sharing partner (%): 1.70% for me and my colleagues.   2. 20% for you as a partner/fronting for us.  3. 10% for expenses that may be incurred by both parties in connection with this transaction.  Our law prohibits a civil servant from maintaining an offshore account, which is why we are contacting you. If you are satisfied with this proposal, please provide the following information as soon as possible: 1. The name you wish to use as the beneficiary of the fund.   2. Your confidential telephone and fax numbers.   Further discussion will focus on how the fund will be donated and full details on how to leverage this great opportunity of ours.  Thank you and God bless you.   Best regards, George Osawa - Irish Linux Users Group: ilug@linux.ie http://www.linux.ie/mailman/listinfo/ilug for information about (un)subscriptions. Date: Fri Sep 6, 2002 11:12:45 To: zzzzason@cpan.org Subject: Industry Forum #136 MIME Version: 1.0 Content Transfer Encoding: 7-bit Message ID: PM200011:12:45 AM Content Type: multipart/linked; border="----=_NextPart_QXVROEFEFX" This is an HTML email.  If you see this message, your email client does not support HTML messages.  ------=_NextPart_QXVROEFEFX Content Type: text/html;charset="iso-8859-1" Content Transfer Encoding: 7 bits   Minute Man II Industry Forum 160 lbs. light - no electricity required - complete set under $6,000! Now anyone can become a pianist!     A small one-off project? The answer is Froth-Pak! The smallest, self-contained, ready-to-use foam for repairs and minor work! Also available: Insta-Stick Tilebond RoofPak and more!    Get your copy of the industry catalog! The most complete references for our industry!   Click on the photo above to learn more about the equipment!         Industry Forum Number 136 10341 Forum Members #136-1: Dik M PA It would be much more helpful to the industry if SPFA could help find a "CODE COMPLIANT" fire barrier for attic spaces etc. rather than a lecture on fast and loose applications code. Something about 30 cents (BD. FT.) installed, meeting all codes and sprays used. Many companies we talk to have a product that seems great BUT they haven't spent the money testing the foam. Perhaps a small committee could assess the performance of various products and report the results to the SPFA, which would in turn "raise funding" from the US.  #136-2 William B Australia We are in Australia but are having a hard time locating polyurea sprayers here so we can start the PDA chapter. Do you have any list of Australian contractors/suppliers????or perhaps they can raise their hand and let us know at enviroline@powerup.com.aufor the good of the gameit is imperative that the association informs customers and specifiers of applications and properties polyureas and trained its members also to keep away the cowboys who are giving the industry a bad name  #136-3 Ed M. I am an aviation magazine writer and one of them is new Test International publication, which was released this month. I need any new processes that can be applied to aircraft, especially commercial aviation. #136-4 John C Louisiana I have a Graco Foam Cat 2000 and a Probler gun with a 01 tip. I use this setup to spray truck bed liners. My question is: Can and how can I spray foam insulation with my equipment? What are the different types of insulation?  #136-5 Murph Mahaffey Glas-Craft I like the new look of the Industry Forum!  #136-6 Mark W South Carolina I'm tired of all this nonsense about covering foam with a "thermal barrier". What the hell do you think a marshmallow is? If you're saying that anything that can be FORCED to burn should be covered with a FIRE RESISTANT barrier, then you better start covering all those trusses, joists and plywood that are definitely NOT first class fire rated. This double standard regarding foam comes directly from those who stand to lose business from it. Icynene is DIFFERENT. DOES NOT BURN ALONE. IT DOES NOT MELT. DOES NOT EMIT PHOSGENE. Does it smoke during a fire? Sure, so what? Blaming the foam in the attic for a house fire because it causes the foam to ultimately burn is as foolish as blaming the foam seat cushions for catching fire when the gas tank bursts and burns the car. Get real inspectors. You want us to cover the only thing in the attic that DOESN'T BURN! As for the infamous R rating system, THIS IS COMPLETELY FALSE. The test is designed to make porous insulation appear to perform better than it actually does. By only measuring conductivity and ignoring convection and radiant transfer to convection, the test should be thrown out for the industry lackey, and that was 20 years ago with that outdated fiberglass junk that everyone is still selling. There's a reason they don't make refrigerators, freezers, coolers, and coffee cups out of fiberglass or cellulose. Think about it.  #136-7 Dirk Benthien Forum Moderator Thank you to Marek and Dik for the above comments. I also feel that far too often individuals and companies become complacent and quietly live by the rules and regulations without trying to change them even when everyone knows they make no sense. We are all experts and representatives of this industry and we should speak up and promote change!  #136-8 Martin S Canada Does anyone make a machine that dispenses a crumb rubber/urethane blend?   #136-9 Carole L California re #135-8 Otto V Germany What are the answers? (Recall 141b)  #136-10 Brian D Canada  There is a lot of talk about ceramic coatings. We are a distributor of such a coating. We have never subscribed to R-20. Reason = ASTM test is not available to measure the R-value of coatings. We compare standard insulation to ceramic coatings using BTU loss calculations. Depending on your criteria, we can get anywhere from 2 to 3 inches of standard aluminum jacketed insulation. We have the data and projects to prove it.  #136-11 CPI We have had inquiries from many people regarding used equipment - particularly the Gusmer H20/35 H2000 H2 GX-7 and Glas-Craft Probler. Please contact me at 805-552-9128.++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ End of message. Date: Sun 08 Sep 2002 15:29:20 +0200 (CEST) From: =?iso-8859-1?q?ackou=20acke=20martin=20francis?= Subject: I NEED URGENT HELP POSSIBLE.TEL:+ 225 05775748 To: zzzz@jmason.org Version MIME: 1.0 Content Type: Text/Plain; charset=iso-8859-1 Content transfer encoding: 8-bit MR MARTIN FRANCIS ABIDJAN COTE DIVOIRE WEST AFRICA TEL: +225 05775748. URGENT AND NOBLE PROPOSAL FOR A DIRECTOR. DEAR, I would like to warmly greet you and your entire family. I received your contact from the Ivory Coast Chamber of Commerce. I prayed about it and chose your name over others because of its respectful nature. Moreover, after my strong prayers and fasting, God reveals to me that you are a straightforward, honest and Godly person. This is the reason why I never waste my time to offer you this business for our mutual benefits. In fact, you will never regret it, as long as you give me the best possible hand to work with. Believe me.  My name is MARTIN FRANCIS, citizen of the coast divoire and only child of the late Mr. and Mrs. FRANCIS. My late father was a former financial controller of a telecommunications company in Cte d'Ivoire (CITELCOM). My father died in recent years due to the heated political crisis in my country. But I am motherless because my fathers were late and my mother's death on SEPTEMBER 26, 1993 was the result of a spiritual attack by a member of our family who hated her only because of my father's wealth. Moreover, they also tried their part against my father and me, but negatively because God Almighty is on our side. Indeed, God is wonderful. Although before my father's death in one of the private hospitals here, he secretly revealed to me specifically family matters and above all the safety of his money, 16,500,000.00 dollars (sixteen million five hundred thousand US dollars) that he deposited in a bank here in my Abidjan county Cte dIvoire and I used my surname MARTIN FRANCIS as the closest relative of the deposits. This amount came from an inflated contract for the construction of an underground telephone network to replace the previous one in the new city (Yamoussoukro) and other large cities, as well as for the installation of a microwave station, awarded to my late father, Mr. JOSEPH FRANCIS in 1999 to expatriate companies. In fact, after completing the payment of the contract workers, my late father deposited this fund in the bank as the full executor-beneficiary of the said company (CITELCOM). This is a fund that I want to transfer to your account as a contractor-beneficiary due for payment provided that you cooperate. Therefore, I am appealing to you for your full and urgent assistance in telegraphic transfer of these sixteen million five hundred thousand US dollars, 16,500,000 dollars US to the account of your choice to ensure a very good business investment in your country as instructed by my father before he was late. I require the following from you.  1. Your personal phone and fax number for easy and close communication 2. Your bank number to efficiently and effectively transfer this money to your designated account 3. You must make the necessary arrangements for me to meet you immediately after the funds are transferred to your account and confirmed by you. 4.You must provide me with a college in your country to continue my education.  5. You will have to be my guardian and part of the joint venture investment when I reach your country.  In addition, my late father instructed me to donate 20% of the total amount to someone to help me pass on this fund.  Furthermore, I would like to assure you that this transaction will be finalized within the next (3) days in which you express your willingness to assist me. I suggest that this transaction be conducted in strict confidence because I have worked out all the conditions regarding the transfer of this fund.  I request and kindly request you to expedite this transaction as soon as possible as my late father instructed me not to invest this money in this country, Cote d'Ivoire. That I should invest abroad as per my choice for my own benefit and security reasons.  Thank you very much while waiting for confirmation of this business proposal and please do not hesitate to contact me immediately after receiving this message with my direct phone number mentioned above tel: +225 05775748 so that we can proceed immediately. Please and please don't disappoint.  I am waiting for your urgent answer, thank you very much again and God bless you.  Best regards, MARTIN FRANCIS.         ____________________________________________________________ Is Yahoo!? -- Une adresse @yahoo.fr is free and en franais ! Peasant! Date: Sun, 08 Sep 2002 23:07:56 +1000 MIME version: 1.0 Content type: text/plain; charset="iso-8859-1" X-Priority: 3 (Normal) X-Msmail Priority: Normal X-Mailer: The Bat! (v1.52f) Business Importance: Normal Content Transfer Encoding: 8 bit It was the spring of 1979. I was a tall, goofy-looking kid in middle school with buck teeth and freckles.  Every day in the cafeteria I went from table to table... I stole other children's lunch money.  No, I didn't rob them with a gun or a knife - I just made a little deal with them.  I'll borrow two dollars today, I said, and I'll bring you five dollars next week.  The investment was too good to pass up, and the other kids were throwing their lunch money at me like gravy on mashed potatoes.  Of course, when "next week" rolled around and I couldn't come up with the cash, I promised I would pay them even more the following week if they would let me hold on to my investment a little longer.  Finally, the end of the year came and high school began, and with it came girls and homework and parties and sports, and these poor eighth-grade kids had more on their minds than last year's lunch money.  I escaped with a decent sum of money for a high school student and they didn't even beat me up.  This story contains two of the greatest stock market secrets you will ever know.  First, greed is your number one enemy. You won't turn $2 into $5 in a week, so cash out when you get ahead.  Don't wait until the boat sinks before grabbing a life jacket.  Second, never trust any investment advisor. They count on their money, not yours.  The "professionals", those rigid investment advisors and money managers, will always tell you that the best time to buy is NOW.  According to these guys, the longer you keep your money in the market, the more money you will make. Ask them when is the best time to sell and their answer is NEVER.    In a sense they are right.  If you put $250,000 in an index fund now, you'll probably have over a million dollars in thirty or forty years.  But here's the problem: do you want to WAIT thirty or forty years to be rich?  Hell no!  You want your money NOW  so you can enjoy it. It's hard to enjoy your assets when you're seventy and in a wheelchair.  If you could make a million dollars in the next few years, what would you do with it?  Where would you travel?  What car would you buy?    The fact is... youth is the best time to be rich.  If your goal is to make quick profits in the market, volatility is your ally and stability is your enemy.  You want to see these big two-hundred-point gains a day and then a week later a four-hundred-point crash.  You don't care if the market is up 20% this year, as long as it was UNSTABLE.  This way you will earn money.  I'm talking about day trading here.    My father invests in the traditional way; it has good shares and is going up by 30 thousand. and drops by 30 thousand. In the long run, 5-10 years, it makes money.   A day trader buys or sells 5,000 shares of XYZ for a profit of $25,000 in a 5-10 minute trade.  It works quickly, using all available information about a specific stock and assessing whether it will rise or fall in a matter of hours or sometimes minutes.    I can teach you how to do it and how to make amazing amounts of money doing it.  It's not rocket science and you just need to learn a few basic principles to get started.  Society would have you believe that successful trading is complicated and requires formal training.    The truth is that rich people use very simple investment strategies to make money.    Popular media and investment professionals portray successful trading as difficult and complex in order to scare you out of the boxing ring.  They don't want competition, and they certainly don't want you paying a few dollars to an online trading company to complete a transaction that would cost them forty or fifty dollars.  They only make money if you believe two lies: 1) That investing is too difficult and risky for the average person.  2) Using an investment advisor who charges a high commission is safer than investing online for a few dollars per trade.  Here's what the financial gurus in today's society absolutely DON'T WANT YOU TO KNOW... Profitable day trading strategies are actually so simple that anyone can do it - as long as they put in a few hours to learn.    After reading over 200 financial books and publications over the last decade and using day trading to make over four million dollars in the stock market, I have come to the following conclusions: **Achieving financial success is incredibly simple.  **Anyone can do it.  **Learning only takes a few hours.  When I discovered the secret of day trading, I didn't become rich overnight.  If you want an instant cash transfer to Wal-Mart.  Buy a ski mask and a shotgun and rob the local bank. The only way to get rich quickly or otherwise is through hard work, knowledge and determination.  After learning the basics of day trading, I started practicing the art of trading itself and the first few weeks brought modest profits.  The next few months gave me the hands-on experience I needed to really make a living, and I was approaching a six-figure income. In less than three years, with no formal financial education, with minimal effort and moderate risk, I made my first million.  I want to share the knowledge I gained during these creative years of trading with you in my new book Master Trader.  You will learn from my mistakes and successes as I teach you the simple, secret day trading formula that I have used profitably year after year.  A day trader's earnings can be astonishing.  Thousands or even hundreds of thousands of dollars can be made or lost in a matter of minutes.  The difference between making money and losing your shirt is simply this: knowledge.  I will pass on this knowledge to you and give you an edge in this high stakes game.   Average day trader income: 5% average income over $500,000 per year 22% average income over $250,000 per year 35% average income over $100,000 per year.  27% average income from $50,000 to $99,999 per year 11% average income from $20,000 to $49,999 per year After reading Master Trader, you will discover extremely profitable, simple yet powerful trading methods that will give you an almost unfair trading advantage and will make you win DESPITE the current market weakness.   Here's an excerpt of what I'll teach you: ***Make money whether stocks go up or down.   ***Learn how to get in and out of stocks in a split second.   *** Find out exactly what stocks to trade, the exact price to buy them and the exact price to sell them.    *** Save thousands of dollars by learning to avoid beginner mistakes.   *** Learn how to trade stocks like a pro and how to consistently make money in any market!    *** Learn proven strategies that give you the best chance for great success.    *** Profit from large price fluctuations during the day.   ***Earn money on the biggest news.   *** Actively manage risk and learn to achieve maximum profits.    ***Learn how to use the tools and information that Wall Street professionals use.   *** Learn how to develop and maintain a winning state of mind.    It's time to ask yourself: Will I listen to professionals who say BUY, BUY, BUY, but never sell? Or maybe I will take control of my financial future and start making money in the stock market NOW?  Who cares about your economic interests - some wealthy Wall Street stockbroker or you?  With the Master Trader e-book, you will learn everything you need to know to start your Day Trading adventure... from choosing the best broker to take advantage of the lowest commissions and instant order execution, to professional trading strategies that make professional traders millions of dollars.  The Master Trader eBook is the most comprehensive, yet easy to understand and simple book ever written on active trading. If you are serious about success in short-term stock trading - ORDER TODAY and start paving the way to your own financial future.  Oh, and remember that skinny kid in eighth grade? His high school friends laughed when he said he was going to make money in the stock market.    Six years later, he bought a beach house on the California coast - FOR CASH.  Oops, they weren't laughing anymore.  In the rollercoaster market we have today, day trading is the fastest path to wealth.  If you're looking for a long-term retirement investment without the risk growing at 5% per year, this is definitely not the game for you.  However, if you want the FASTEST possible way to make a fortune in the market with the lowest risk, order the MASTER TRADER e-book now.  I promise to teach you ALL the secrets that helped me become a millionaire through successful day trading.  You don't need to know anything about the market and anyone can do it with minimal effort.  It's easy to win this game if you know how the pieces move. Date: Tue Sep 10 2002 04:13:50 -1100 MIME Version: 1.0 Content Type: Text/Plain; charset="iso-8859-1" X Priority: 3 (Normal) X-Msmail Priority: Normal X-Mailer: Webmail Service (5.5.2650.21) Meaning: Normal Content Transfer Encoding: 8 bits It was the spring of 1979. I was just a tall, goofy-looking kid in middle school with buck teeth and freckles.  Every day in the cafeteria I went from table to table... I stole other children's lunch money.  No, I didn't rob them with a gun or a knife - I just made a little deal with them.  I'll borrow two dollars today, I said, and I'll bring you five dollars next week.  The investment was too good to pass up, and the other kids were throwing their lunch money at me like gravy on mashed potatoes.  Of course, when "next week" rolled around and I couldn't come up with the cash, I promised I would pay them even more the following week if they would let me hold on to my investment a little longer.  Finally, the end of the year came and high school began, and with it came girls and homework and parties and sports, and these poor eighth-grade kids had more on their minds than last year's lunch money.  I escaped with a decent sum of money for a high school student and they didn't even beat me up.  This story contains two of the greatest stock market secrets you will ever know.  First, greed is your number one enemy. You won't turn $2 into $5 in a week, so cash out when you get ahead.  Don't wait until the boat sinks before grabbing a life jacket.  Second, never trust any investment advisor. They count on their money, not yours.  The "professionals", those rigid investment advisors and money managers, will always tell you that the best time to buy is NOW.  According to these guys, the longer you keep your money in the market, the more money you will make. Ask them when is the best time to sell and their answer is NEVER.    In a sense they are right.  If you put $250,000 in an index fund now, you'll probably have over a million dollars in thirty or forty years.  But here's the problem: do you want to WAIT thirty or forty years to be rich?  Hell no!  You want your money NOW  so you can enjoy it. It's hard to enjoy your assets when you're seventy and in a wheelchair.  If you could make a million dollars in the next few years, what would you do with it?  Where would you travel?  What car would you buy?    The fact is... youth is the best time to be rich.  If your goal is to make quick profits in the market, volatility is your ally and stability is your enemy.  You want to see these big two-hundred-point gains a day and then a week later a four-hundred-point crash.  You don't care if the market is up 20% this year, as long as it was UNSTABLE.  This way you will earn money.  I'm talking about day trading here.    My father invests in the traditional way; it has good shares and is going up by 30 thousand. and drops by 30 thousand. In the long run, 5-10 years, it makes money.   A day trader buys or sells 5,000 shares of XYZ for a profit of $25,000 in a 5-10 minute trade.  It works quickly, using all available information about a specific stock and assessing whether it will rise or fall in a matter of hours or sometimes minutes.    I can teach you how to do it and how to make amazing amounts of money doing it.  It's not rocket science and you just need to learn a few basic principles to get started.  Society would have you believe that successful trading is complicated and requires formal training.    The truth is that rich people use very simple investment strategies to make money.    Popular media and investment professionals portray successful trading as difficult and complex in order to scare you out of the boxing ring.  They don't want competition, and they certainly don't want you paying a few dollars to an online trading company to complete a transaction that would cost them forty or fifty dollars.  They only make money if you believe two lies: 1) That investing is too difficult and risky for the average person.  2) Using an investment advisor who charges a high commission is safer than investing online for a few dollars per trade.  Here's what the financial gurus in today's society absolutely DON'T WANT YOU TO KNOW... Profitable day trading strategies are actually so simple that anyone can do it - as long as they put in a few hours to learn.    After reading over 200 financial books and publications over the last decade and using day trading to make over four million dollars in the stock market, I have come to the following conclusions: **Achieving financial success is incredibly simple.  **Anyone can do it.  **Learning only takes a few hours.  When I discovered the secret of day trading, I didn't become rich overnight.  If you want an instant cash transfer to Wal-Mart.  Buy a ski mask and a shotgun and rob the local bank. The only way to get rich quickly or otherwise is through hard work, knowledge and determination.  After learning the basics of day trading, I started practicing the art of trading itself and the first few weeks brought modest profits.  The next few months gave me the hands-on experience I needed to really make a living, and I was approaching a six-figure income. In less than three years, with no formal financial education, with minimal effort and moderate risk, I made my first million.  I want to share the knowledge I gained during these creative years of trading with you in my new book Master Trader.  You will learn from my mistakes and successes as I teach you the simple, secret day trading formula that I have used profitably year after year.  A day trader's earnings can be astonishing.  Thousands or even hundreds of thousands of dollars can be made or lost in a matter of minutes.  The difference between making money and losing your shirt is simply this: knowledge.  I will pass on this knowledge to you and give you an edge in this high stakes game.   Average day trader income: 5% average income over $500,000 per year 22% average income over $250,000 per year 35% average income over $100,000 per year.  27% average income from $50,000 to $99,999 per year 11% average income from $20,000 to $49,999 per year After reading Master Trader, you will discover extremely profitable, simple yet powerful trading methods that will give you an almost unfair trading advantage and will make you win DESPITE the current market weakness.   Here's an excerpt of what I'll teach you: ***Make money whether stocks go up or down.   ***Learn how to get in and out of stocks in a split second.   *** Find out exactly what stocks to trade, the exact price to buy them and the exact price to sell them.    *** Save thousands of dollars by learning to avoid beginner mistakes.   *** Learn how to trade stocks like a pro and how to consistently make money in any market!    *** Learn proven strategies that give you the best chance for great success.    *** Profit from large price fluctuations during the day.   ***Earn money on the biggest news.   *** Actively manage risk and learn to achieve maximum profits.    ***Learn how to use the tools and information that Wall Street professionals use.   *** Learn how to develop and maintain a winning state of mind.    It's time to ask yourself: Will I listen to professionals who say BUY, BUY, BUY, but never sell? Or maybe I will take control of my financial future and start making money in the stock market NOW?  Who cares about your economic interests - some wealthy Wall Street stockbroker or you?  With the Master Trader e-book, you will learn everything you need to know to start your Day Trading adventure... from choosing the best broker to take advantage of the lowest commissions and instant order execution, to professional trading strategies that make professional traders millions of dollars.  The Master Trader eBook is the most comprehensive, yet easy to understand and simple book ever written on active trading. If you are serious about success in short-term stock trading - ORDER TODAY and start paving the way to your own financial future.  Oh, and remember that skinny kid in eighth grade? His high school friends laughed when he said he was going to make money in the stock market.    Six years later, he bought a beach house on the California coast - FOR CASH.  Oops, they weren't laughing anymore.  In the rollercoaster market we have today, day trading is the fastest path to wealth.  If you're looking for a long-term retirement investment without the risk growing at 5% per year, this is definitely not the game for you.  However, if you want the FASTEST possible way to make a fortune in the market with the lowest risk, order the MASTER TRADER e-book now.  I promise to teach you ALL the secrets that helped me become a millionaire through successful day trading.  You don't need to know anything about the market and anyone can do it with minimal effort.  It's easy to win this game if you know how the pieces move. This has created a completely new market in the Indian cable industry. After the entry into force of this act, cable television operators will be obliged to distribute paid channels via set-top boxes. There are an estimated 38 million cable TV households in India! Implementing this change will require huge investments in conditional access software in set-top boxes and modernization of the headend network - this is a great opportunity for you to take advantage of this huge market! Sep 9, 2002 23:16:35 To: social@linux.ie MIME version: 1.0 Content type: text/plain;charset="iso-8859-1" Content transfer encoding: 7-bit Subject: [ ILUG- Social] urgent help From: social-admin@linux.ie Errors-To: social-admin@linux.ie X-Mailman version: 1.1 Precedence: collective List ID: Irish Linux User Group Social Events X-Beenthere: social@linux.ie ATTN: I'm Edward Mulete JR. son of Mr. STEVE MBEKI MULETE from Zimbabwe. I'm sorry this email will surprise you, even though we don't know my mother. Mrs. Clara. You found the contact through her private search. Due to the current war against white farmers in Zimbabwe and President Robert Mugabe's support to curry favor with all white owned farms in our country in order to gain favor for re-election.  All white farmers were asked to hand over their farms to the government for redistribution and indeed to members of his political party and my father, although the black was the treasurer of the farmers' association and a strong member of the opposition party that did not support President Idea. He then ordered members of his party and the police under his pay to invade my father's farm and burn everything on the farm. They killed my Father and took many things from his farm. After my father died, our local pastor and a close friend of my father gave us his will documents with my father's instructions that we should leave Zimbabwe in case something happened to him. Will documents have a deposit certificate confirming the deposit. Kept for us by an unknown security company. To the company that its contents are money, therefore it was deposited as personal effects and ensures that we do not stay here as we could be easily found. by his enemies. The total amount is USD 21.5 million. We are therefore asking for your help to transfer the fund out of Zimbabwe as our fate and future are far from reality, hence this email to you. The president's current ban on the international press in Zimbabwe and his resignation as Minister of Finance to avoid issuing transfer permits in excess of $1 million to white farmers are just a few of the unthinkable things he is committing in my country. I tried to contact my father's close friend, Mr. John Casahans from Australia, also a farmer who was traveling with us to Zimbabwe but left with his family late last year after this unpleasant incident, to no avail. If you are interested in helping, please contact me immediately via email to facilitate communication and I will provide you with the time frame and terms of the transaction. We have come up with a great plan to take care of your transfer within two weeks. Please note that this transaction is 100% confidential and risk-free and poses no risk to you or us in any way. We have decided to give you 20% of the total amount after confirming the fund in any account of your choice, in case taxation will not require much use of the money, and we look forward to coming to your country to invest our share and settle there. I will provide you with a private telephone number so that our conversation is 100% confidential.  Please do not use the reply button, only reply to Edmulete7@netscape.net. Please pay attention.  May God truly bless you as you help yourself and us.  Mr EDWARD MULETE - Irish Linux Users Group Social Events: social@linux.ie http://www.linux.ie/mailman/listinfo/social for information on (un)subscriptions. List maintainer: listmaster@linux.ie

Date: Tue 10 Sep 2002 16:17:30 +0200 Content transfer encoding: 8-bit message ID: Subject: [ILUG] Looking for a partner From: ilug-admin@linux.ie Errors-to: ilug-admin@linux .ie X-Mailman-Version: 1.1 Precedence: Bulk List ID: Irish Linux User Group X-Beenthere: ilug@linux.ie Dear Be First Partner I must apologize for using this medium to communicate with you about this project.  I am a high-ranking official of the Nigerian government and a founding member of the ruling party, currently the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP).  My committee  the Niger Delta Development Corporation (NDDC)  which is responsible for managing and supervising the disbursement of oil revenues to the Nigerian government. The income under our control reaches several hundred million dollars a month. I and other colleagues from NDDC currently need a foreign partner to whose bank account we will transfer the amount of forty-nine million five hundred thousand US dollars ($49.5 million). This fund fell to us. as commission for crude oil sales contracts executed under our supervision.  The Fund is currently pending in a government account called CBN/FGN INDEPENDENT REVENUE number 400-939134 at J.P.MORGAN CHASE BANK New York. You can do this independently. However, due to our position as civil servants and members of the NDDC, we cannot raise these funds on our behalf. This is because as top government officials we cannot currently legally hold or operate bank accounts outside our country.  I was delegated by my colleagues as part of the trust to look for a foreign partner to whose account we would transfer the funds. Hence the reason for this email. We will transfer the money to your account with your company when we present yours as a registered foreign company in Nigeria and you have received payment for the contract you have performed for our country through the NDDC and any other Federal Ministry through which we choose to use to withdraw funds.  For support and partnership, please reply to negotiate the fees or percentage you would like to receive once the funds arrive in your bank account.  However, please note that this transaction regarding our instructions to continue our relationship is subject to these terms and conditions. First, our belief in your transparency. Second, treat this transaction with the utmost secrecy and confidentiality. Finally, and most importantly, you will be provided with an account that you have complete control over.  The transaction, though discreet, is legal and does not involve any risk or legal drawback for either us or you, now or in the future, as we have introduced excellent machines that will ensure hassle-free transfer to your account once approved.  The transfer will be made to your account within ten-fourteen (10-14) business days, once we have reached an agreement and you have provided me with the appropriate bank account and company name and address with all contact numbers, including fax number.  I look forward to working with you and ask that you maintain confidentiality in this transaction. Please send me your reply by mail.  Best regards, Anderson K. Eseimoku - Irish Linux Users Group: ilug@linux.ie http://www.linux.ie/mailman/listinfo/ilug for information about (un)subscriptions. List maintainer: listmaster@linux.ie

Date: Wed 11 Sep 2002 06:12:39 -0500 From: "Wesley Gee" Priority X: 3 To: ilug@linux.ie MIME Version: 1.0 Content Type: Text/Plain; charset=us-ascii Content transfer encoding: 7-bit Subject: [ILUG] DON'T throw away your life insurance From: ilug-admin@linux.ie Errors-to: ilug-admin@linux.ie X-Mailman version: 1.1 Precedence : collective List ID: Irish Linux User Group X-Beenthere: ilug@linux.ie Dear ilug@linux.ie Life Partners are life insurance appraisers who value all types of life insurance policies, allowing people to access their life insurance cash now, rather than later. We help individuals unlock cash from unused assets.  Typical candidates are individuals who are typically 65 years of age or older and find that their financial and/or estate planning needs have changed. Financial advisors have advised some candidates to us to cancel their life insurance policies so that they can invest their money in a vehicle that will now give them a return. DON'T cancel your policy because it could be worth it NOW.  Why do people sell their policies?  The reasons why people decide to sell their life insurance policies are as varied as the people themselves. Some reasons include: Pay off debt Long-term care insurance fund Eliminate costly premiums Take advantage of other financial options Donate to charity Help family members Life partners Living Solutions Traditionally, life insurance provides benefits only after death. With Life Partners, you can provide cash benefits for life!     Life Partners Goals To provide market ratings to life insurance policyholders Provide quotes for qualified policies Provide lump sum cash payments to qualified owners Eliminate costly premium payments Contact us now for a FREE quote on your life insurance policy.  REMEMBER THAT THIS IS A FREE SERVICE AND NO COSTS ARE INVOLVED!!  1-866-686-LIFE 1-866-686-5433 or email us at llhjr55@yahoo.com with your name and phone number and one of our team members will contact you ASAP.   If you wish to be removed please send a message "remove" to llhjr55@yahoo.com - Irish Linux Users Group: ilug@linux.ie http://www.linux.ie/mailman/listinfo/ilug for (un) information about subscription. List maintainer: listmaster@linux.ie

Date: Thu. Sep 12, 2002 13:44:13 -0700 Date: Thu. Sep 12, 2002 13:44:13 -0700 United Kingdom Tel/fax: 44-870-136-7079 Date: 11/09/2002 FROM: CAPTAIN JOHN OKELE DEAR MRS. I received my contact information from a military friend with whom I trained in your country. I'm the captain. JOHN OKELE, former Commander of the Security Guard of the late Laurent Kabila (former President of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (Africa)) currently in exile with his wife and one child in remote Leicester City, UK due to threats from the current government headed by the deceased's son Laurent Kabila that he will kill my life and my family, saying that I know about his father's death. I assisted the late President Laurent Kabila in storing $35 million (thirty-five million) in a security company during the war in my country, although the security company does not know the contents of the deposited boxes because we deposit them as your personal effects. Laurent Kabila. I am therefore appealing to you to help me invest these funds before the current government, headed by my son, knows about this money to avoid it being taken away.   After completing this transaction, I will compensate you with 45% of the fund while 5% will be used for any expenses we should incur for the transaction and the remaining amount should be used to open an account for my family to invest there with your help.   I need a profitable long-term investment plan for your company or you. Your suggestions and ideas regarding conditions are urgently needed.   I expect a quick response. Please also provide me with your current email address. Telephone/fax numbers (private) to contact you.   NOTE: Please call or fax the above line which belongs to my cousin as he knows my confidentiality. You can contact me directly at my email above. Date: Sep 12, 2002 18:21:31 -0000 Message ID: Reply to: news@risingtidestudios.com Organization X: Venture Reporter From: "Venture Reporter" To: "zzzz@jmason.org" Subject: Invite: Summit on Content Management, October 10, New York. MIME version: 1.0. Content type: text/html; charset=US-ASCII This email is sent to zzzz@jmason.org. To unsubscribe, visit http://www.venturereporter.net/myaccount/. If you ever have trouble deleting or changing your email subscriptions to our newsletters or contacting us, please do not hesitate to send an email to support@venturereporter.net and a specialist will contact you immediately. Venture Reporter 307 West 36th Street 10th Floor New York New York 10018 Phone: 646.473.2222 Online content company.                                Dear Friends The online content industry is doing fantastically well.      Sounds crazy? Maybe.  Due to the continued disregard for advertising on the Internet over the past two years, content websites have resorted to laying off employees and discontinuing their offerings.      But this terrible environment has spawned an undeniable trend: content companies requiring people to pay for content.  Finally, after five years of freedom, people are starting to understand that on the Internet, just like in the real world, you get what you pay for, and they are taking out their credit cards.  According to the Online Publishers Association, U.S. consumers spent $675 million on paid content online last year, a 92% increase in spending compared to spending levels in 2000. This number is expected to increase exponentially this year.  Take a look at these success stories: New York Times Digital has steadily expanded its paid content services over the past year and saw a 16 percent increase in its total revenue in the most recent quarter.                  TheStreet.com brought in more than $3 million in subscriptions last quarter, up nearly 50 percent from the year-ago quarter.                  By the end of this year, ConsumerReports.com will reach more than one million paying subscribers.                  Consumer media subscription service RealNetworks has more than 750,000 subscribers, which brought in $17.8 million in the most recent quarter.                  The Wall Street Journal Online added more than 6,000 new paying customers last quarter, increasing its subscriber base to 646,000. FT.com added 17,000 subscribers in the three months after launching its premium site in May.            In recognition of this trend, we are hosting the third installment of our innovative Content Management Summit on October 10, 2002. This event highlights the shift in the content industry from free to paid subscription services and the technologies that enable content management and monetization.      Our previous Content Management Summit (also known as the Digital Rights Summit), held on October 18 last year in New York and January 29 in Los Angeles, was an unqualified success.      The 3rd Content Management Summit, taking place on October 10, 2002 in New York City at Millennium Broadway, will bring together 100 executives from leading content and distribution companies for a day of networking and discovering practical solutions.      The event will include presentations by software and service companies providing services and solutions in the field of sales, distribution, management and content protection.      We are excited that Microsoft TeleKnowledge eMeta and Liquify will be showcasing their latest products and services.      The event will also feature six intimate roundtables focusing on various aspects of online content.  These panels are intended to provide an informal forum to discuss the challenges facing these specific vertical markets, changes in the sectors since the collapse of the internet industry, and best practices in the industry.  The panels will feature leading practitioners from each sector and will also include an interactive Q&A session with the audience.      The roundtable topics will include: Online blogs: their impact on large media companies in terms of editorial as well as content delivery/production mechanisms.                  Financial news and information companies: How they use technology to deliver content to users and how the economics have changed since the stock market crash.                  Business information services like Hoovers Lexis-Nexis and others: best practices for marketing niche products and industry revenue streams.                  Daily news/newspaper publishers publishing online: including how speed dictates technology choices and the shift towards paid content and its implications.                  Consumer and entertainment publishers: How publishers determine the value of entertainment content, the emphasis on paid subscriptions, online advertising and other issues.            We invite you to this very important event on October 10.  If you are directly responsible for managing content on a large content site, you may qualify for a VIP ticket.  Please email your request with your name and biography to invitation@cmsummit.com.  If you are working with a software or service provider or someone who is not directly responsible for purchasing software or content management solutions, you can purchase a ticket to this event for $1,200 at invitation@cmsummit.com.        Sincerely, Jason McCabe Calacanis Editor-in-Chief and CEO Venture Reporter and Silicon Alley Reporter This email goes to zzzz@jmason.org.    If you do not want to receive these rare updates, simply click here and you will be immediately deleted.   You can also click the link here or cut and paste it into your browser: http://venturereporter.net/myaccount/k.asp?E=jm@jmason.org  Venture Reporter 307 West 36th Street 10th Floor New York New York 10018 Phoe: 646.473 .2222

Date: Mon. Sep 16, 2002 09:33:38 +0200 X Priority: 1 X-Mailer: Microsoft Outlook Express 5.00.2919.6900 DM MIME Version: 1.0 Content Type: Text/Plain; charset="us-ascii" X-MIME-Autoconversion: from quoted print to 8bit via Lugh.tuatha.org id IAA25119 Subject: [ILUG] MICHAEL ! ilug From: ilug-admin@linux.ie Errors-To: ilug-admin@linux.ie X-Mailman Version: 1.1 Precedence: Bulk List ID: Irish Linux User Group X-Beenthere: ilug@linux.ie Content -Transfer Encoding : 8-bit ilug from Mr. Michael Kamah and family in Johannesburg, South Africa.  My Dear Good morning. This very confidential request should come as a surprise to you. However, due to the nature of what is happening to me and my family, I have insisted that I contact you and I fully understand that this is not the best way to contact you due to the nature of my request and the attention it requires. I received your contact details from your country's information directory while desperately searching for someone who could secretly and confidentially help me move and manage some family fortunes.  My name is Mr Michael Kamah, second son of Mr Smith Kamah from Beitbridge Zimbabwe. At the height of the current political crisis in our country, during which white farmers in our country are being killed and robbed of their belongings by supporters of our president, Mr. Robert G. Mugabe, in his efforts to reclaim all white-owned farms in our country, my father and my older brother were brutally murdered to a painful death on February 13, 2002 in their fight to protect several white farmers who had fled to take shelter in our home. My father during his time on earth was a prominent businessman dealing in diamonds and gold from some foreign countries. He publicly opposes the oil politics and crimes against humanity against white farmers carried out by Robert Mugabe and his supporters, in which they imposed media law restrictions to protect their evil deeds. It was not enough that the president and his supporters, after winning the last undemocratic elections, decided to block and! confiscate all the accounts and assets of our black natives [including my father's assets and accounts] who oppose his policies and provide support to these white farmers, along with the assets of the white farmers themselves that are currently being confiscated. That's why I decided to move my mother and younger sister to South Africa, where we currently live with nothing and no means of subsistence.  During my father's earthly life, he deposited the sum of eight million six hundred thousand United States dollars [US$8,600,000.00] in a cargo box with a financial and security company in the Republic of Togo in exchange for cash and transportation of diamonds and gold with several foreign business clients waiting to instructions for transfer to his destination, which he never followed before he met his untimely death on that faithful day. With this in mind, and as my father's only surviving son, and in light of the current killing bans and confiscation of his property, as one of those who provide support to white farmers in our country, I humbly wish to inform you of my intention to use your name and address to ensure that this fund is withdrawn from Africa to the European office of this financial company and I am also asking for honest and trustworthy assistance to help me clear and place this money there before it is imposed and blocked by the current Mugabe!  regime. My mother currently has a valid document confirming this deposit.  This is what I want you to do for me;  1. I want you to be introduced to the financial and security company as the person I have contacted to help my family for this purpose, under whose name and address I and my mother will give them its office in the Republic of Togo as the person who will settle this money when they transfer it to their office in Europe. 2. To finally help me develop and manage this money in any profitable business in your country for at least three years.   I hope that you will honor this request and consider it with favor and great understanding of our current situation, and that you will be a very honest and trustworthy person. Also keeping in mind the confidential nature of my request, I emphasize that you keep everything to yourself to protect the future of my family and yourself by providing this assistance. Thank you and I look forward to your urgent response as soon as you read this request.  Best regards, Mr. Michael Kamah and family.           -- Irish Linux Users Group: ilug@linux.ie http://www.linux.ie/mailman/listinfo/ilug for information about (un)subscriptions. List maintainer: listmaster@linux.ie

These poor choices and behavioral disorders, combined with the unnecessary burden it places on taxpaying citizens in the form of welfare abuses and prison overcrowding, are the primary causes of the cycle of rampant poverty and lack of direction that currently exists in young "black America" today. Milosevic The goal of freedom is the destruction of the Socialist Party of Serbia.         Although, due to the same views, at one time the most polar socialist after the president of this party, prof. Branislav Ivkovic was expelled from the SPS ranks, and today the SPS leadership uses increasingly strict qualifications at the expense of its president, without fear that any of them may be expelled from the party.         In recent days, it is not uncommon for the party leadership to hear that Slobodan Milosevic is not the party and that he does not represent the party, but that the party is the leadership and management board of this party.         However, not everything is going according to the management's plans among the party's members and supporters.         Estimates even say that Bata Zivojinovic will win only 1% of the votes in the September elections.  Most party members still believe in their hero, Slobodan Milosevic.         According to party members, currently those in the party leadership who in recent years disinformed the party's president are trying to save themselves by eliminating president Slobodan Milosevic when they realized that they had made the call. Thus, during performances before municipal boards, you can hear convincing speeches by Dejan Stjepanovic and Igor Raicevic, as well as some of Milinka Isakovi from the ranks of young socialists, members of the organizational and political committee of the SPS president. The position of the Young Socialists' leadership differs from the position of the youth council, which also sides with the president. They are trying in every possible way to marginalize the group of young people who support him. The question is what will happen at the end of this story, but members and supporters will judge the performance of their leaders in the presidential election. Date: Mon Sep  9 12:21:16 2002 Received: via dmail-2002(12) for +lists/freebsd/ports; Mon  9 Sep 2002 12:21:16 -0500 (CDT) Return-Path:  Received: from mx2.freebsd.org (mx2.FreeBSD.org [216.136.204.119]) 	by lerami.lerctr.org (8.12.2/8.12.2/20020902/$Revision: 1.30 $) with ESMTP id g89HL3E9025108 	for ; Mon  9 Sep 2002 12:21:04 -0500 (CDT) Received: from hub.freebsd.org (hub.FreeBSD.org [216.136.204.18]) 	by mx2.freebsd.org (Postfix) with ESMTP 	id 8A8915576D; Mon   9 Sep 2002 10:20:58 -0700 (PDT) 	(envelope-from owner-freebsd-ports@FreeBSD.ORG) Received: by hub.freebsd.org (Postfix  from userid 538) 	id CA0F137B401; Mon   9 Sep 2002 10:20:57 -0700 (PDT) Received: from localhost (localhost [127.0.0.1]) 	by hub.freebsd.org (Postfix) with SMTP 	id B8A822E8017; Mon   9 Sep 2002 10:20:57 -0700 (PDT) Received: by hub.freebsd.org (bulk_mailer v1.12); Mon  9 Sep 2002 10:20:57 -0700 Delivered-To: freebsd-ports@freebsd.org Received: from mx1.FreeBSD.org (mx1.FreeBSD.org [216.136.204.125]) 	by hub.freebsd.org (Postfix) with ESMTP id EE6D037B400 	for ; Mon   9 Sep 2002 10:20:54 -0700 (PDT) Received: from sccrmhc01.attbi.com (sccrmhc01.attbi.com [204.127.202.61]) 	by mx1.FreeBSD.org (Postfix) with ESMTP id 0657243E42 	for ; Mon   9 Sep 2002 10:20:54 -0700 (PDT) 	(envelope-from Books@Books@BlackRealityPublishing.com) Received: from mccrary-8bnedo4 ([24.98.25.152]) by sccrmhc01.attbi.com           (InterMail vM.4.01.03.27 201-229-121-127-20010626) with SMTP           id            for ; Mon  9 Sep 2002 17:20:53 +0000 To:  From:  Subject: Free Excerpt;  Baby Makers  Loser Choosers  & Welfare Abusers...Images of My America! MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=unknown-8bit Message-Id:  Date: Mon  9 Sep 2002 17:20:53 +0000 Sender: owner-freebsd-ports@FreeBSD.ORG List-ID:  List-Archive:  (Web Archive) List-Help:  (List Instructions) List-Subscribe:  List-Unsubscribe:  X-Loop: FreeBSD.org Precedence: bulk X-Virus-Scanned: by amavisd-milter (http://amavis.org/) Status: RO X-Status:  X-Keywords:  X-UID: 3                            Foreword  After thirty?three years of being a black man living in "Ghetto America " an environment notorious for danger  crime  and poverty  I have made startling discoveries involving young African?American men and women who comprise what I have come to define as the "Black Generation X". I have become aware that there is no formal distinction separating young African?Americans from the general definition of "Generation X". Aside from it being regarded as the generation that followed "Baby Boomers"  it's important to point out there is no root definition for this term as well. Since the theme of this work is centered on identifying the realities and misconceptions of young African?American culture  I have chosen a definition that incorporates all of the components that were part of my birth  childhood  and young adult life. Taken from a web site entitled "Generation X"  created and maintained by the Colorado College  the definition is as follows:     "We are a group of people born between 1961 and 1981. We are individuals who live for the 'here and now'  like to experiment  and who require immediate results. We are typically selfish  and cynical  and depend a lot on our parents. We question authority  and feel like we carry the burden of the previous generations. It's that simple. It seems we have come to be called "Xer's" simply because we represent something negative to our elders. We may be the one thing all of the generations that precede us have in common  that is the ability to speak assuredly about our shortcomings. Of course  they overlook the fact that we are their responsibility  or actually their fault. Our generation will be called upon to look after our parents knowing they failed to look after us. Intergenerational justice failed somewhere along the way and it will be our task to either rectify it or make it worse." "We are a group of individuals who grew up with no one at home after school. It appears we have little hope for the future. No jobs  no homes  and basically no money are almost expected of us. These bleak prospects  along with the fact that we will be forced to support the largest amount of senior citizens ever  do not provide much hope. Some believe that these blockades will be too much for us to handle and we will for the most part fail at life  but many see our individualism and resourcefulness that has been built up through our childhood  as our saviors. We will soon discover who is right and who is wrong."   This definition is important because it demonstrates the widely held belief that Generation X is comprised of one core group of American citizens. It over generalizes the similarities it expresses  and applies them to all those who were born within the corresponding years. When in fact these "similarities" speak primarily to only "white" issues and concerns. For instance  "they" say "we" depend a lot on our parents  but in ghetto America "we" could only depend on one our mothers! "They" also say  " . . .we feel like we carry the burden of previous generations " and " . . . we will be forced to support the largest amount of senior citizens ever." In ghetto America  no one ever gives these issues any thought because survival is in the here and now  and is all "we" have time for.  I have known for many years that the differences that separate Generation Xer's black and white occupants would eventually be identified. I never knew I would be the one doing it. Extracting the "Black" from "Generation X" and categorizing it for its own sake is a necessary and important contingency. Without doing so  the social ills that plague Ghetto America would be lost within the generalities that are explained away as part of a collective American identity. There are many hidden truths that exist in black America today. "White America" charges that we spend our time collecting welfare  refusing to vote  reading elementary styled books  watching music videos  day dreaming of becoming rappers  basketball players  selling drugs  and making babies. Much of this is supported in Marlon Riggs's documentary entitled "Ethnic Notions." When African Americans are mentioned  whites typically envision an image that is strikingly similar to the one that graces the cover of this book. A reality that I confirmed while watching "Roger & Me " another documentary written  and directed by Michael Moore. Sadly  many of us have begun to validate this skewed image  while others bend over backwards in an attempt to pretend we do nothing of the kind  only to be contradicted and embarrassed when presented with the daily programming line up for B.E.T. (Black Entertainment Television). Many of us fail to realize  that whatever embarrassment or shame the ex  posed truth may reveal  should be taken as an opportunity to improve  empower  enlighten  and ultimately change anyone who is guilty of perpetrating this kind of behavior. Regarding Black Women: I have known many in my life and although each has had unique attitudes and personalities  I began to notice the majority of them shared the same collective mentality toward black men as a whole-that black men owed them something  and are required to provide and fulfill what was missing from their lives  be it emotional  physical  or economical.  Normally that type of assertion would not warrant opposition from me  so long as a reciprocal attitude was extended. In most cases  it has not been. It's funny though  looking back  I am surprised I never paid any attention to the beliefs and attitudes that different black women subscribe to  or the various schools of thought they possessed. Many have placed strict demands and presumptions on the African?American male  some fair and some unfair. Much of what the public believes and understands about the black female's social structure is often filtered by others in the black community who believe these inaccurate and frequently positive representations will somehow change the reality that is.  What originally sparked my attention was an observation I stumbled upon while skimming through and reading books related to black male and female interaction. I noticed virtually all of the books I read in the genre depict an inaccurate and misleading concentration on the affluent African?American perspective. These stories and commentaries tend to suggest that all African?Americans thrive on a middle?to?upper class professional level. They relay stories of relationship problems with "Huxtable?like" bachelors and bachelorettes whose only concern is why the other has not confessed his or her love. As I read these stories I couldn't help but become irritated by the blatant omission of the prevailing majority of blue collar or "working class" African?Americans. Although there are those in the black community that can identify with the "Huxtable?like" dynamic  unfortunately  they are few and far between.  The majority of stories I have read seem to be geared toward fantasizing and romanticizing the oppressive state of affairs that have plagued Black America. The black authors who have written these books fear the potential backlash awaiting anyone who would dare air out our "dirty laundry". The fact is  truth should never be stifled by fear of any kind.  I recently had a candid conversation with some very dear female friends who stated that although they fully acknowledge the terrible state of affairs many of our women are currently drowning in  they felt that publicizing their predicament would be viewed as a form of betrayal. As our discussion intensified  I reminded them that the only way change can be effected is by increasing public awareness that change is needed  and oftentimes  not exposing the truth can be more crippling than the truth itself.  The purpose of my book is in essence an attempt to change the self?destructive thinking and self?imprisoning behavior that "black male and female generation X" have been subscribing to. While discussing this with my friend  she suggested I simplify my writing style so my potential black readers could better understand what I'm attempting to convey. Acknowledging the real possibility of my message being misunderstood  I suggest to those readers that if they want to fully appreciate the finer points of this narrative-to grab a dictionary. (Don't feel bad-there were several times I had to as well!) Regarding Black Men: An overwhelming number of us have become preoccupied with being cool  buying sports wear  driving expensive cars  wearing gold or platinum jewelry  and often without legitimate personal wealth and while living under the most deplorable conditions! I have chosen to address this rarely acknowledged side of African?American culture because I have lived it. I have seen the chaos and futility that exists on this level. It is a world of ignorance  selfishness  pre?occupation  and idiocy. In my world there are people who applaud a lack of education  who brag about having served time in U.S. penitentiaries  the types of guns they carry  dope peddling  and chasing women. They champion the notion of having children without any regard to the poor environment many of them currently inhabit. In this world  wearing expensive clothes and carrying fancy handbags is mandatory even if it means spending their last dollar in order to look like they've got a million. It's a world where children dress in over?priced sports wear  mimicking and idolizing whatever popular athlete or rapper is currently in the public eye.  Thinking  such as the belief that fancy clothes are what define one's self?worth  and the possible corruption this thinking breeds  seems to not be an important concern for black mothers. It may come as a shock to know that most African?Americans feel that those who don't have the same  if not better  material possessions  are lesser beings  referring to them as being corny  lame  or broke. Even our "male rapper" entertainers promote backward priorities-nothing else matters as long as you look good. "The Big Tymers"  a popular rap duo  have a song called "I'm Still Fly"  shown in heavy rotation on B.E.T. and played regularly on black radio stations throughout the country. ("Fly" is ghetto vernacular for well dressed  also used to describe a female's beauty). Its signature verse asserts:  "I got gator boots with a pimped out Gucci Suit  can't pay my rent cause all my money's spent  but that's O.K. cause I'm still fly."  Worse yet  in the song "Grinding"  the popular duo "Eclipse" glorifies the selling of illegal drugs in inner city neighborhoods as children play and dance throughout the entire video. (The term "grinding" is ghetto vernacular for the selling of illegal drugs) The fact that this song and video is also shown in heavy rotation on B.E.T. is further evidence that our world is in utter turmoil. Some of the key lyrics to this song are "grindingyou know what I keep in the lining" (the area in their coats where they hide illegal drugs) and  "Patty cake Patty cake I'm the bakers man I bake them cakes as fast as I can and you can tell cause of how my bread stack up and I disguise it as rap so the feds backup"  In this verse  the group refers to the process of cooking cocaine and its transformation into cocaine base or crack. When created it is compressed into the form of a large cookie with the average diameter being the size of a typical cake. (hence the term "cake" or sometimes "pie") Unfortunately for the rap genre  this song seems to strengthen the long standing argument posed by most whites that rap music is nothing more than an entertainment medium catering to violent drug offenders  who want and do nothing more than carry guns and break the law.  The negative references I've identified have become an integral part of the urban African?American existence. This mutated reality is ridiculous and unacceptable. This ideology should not be permitted to continue any longer than it already has. There is an overwhelming part of the African?American community that is aware of this crippling mentality. There are also many that are unaware and unfortunately  more that do not even care. Those of us who are in the know have a responsibility to educate and enlighten those of us who are not aware of the negative behavior being perpetrated daily. Whether because of habit or misguided values  this type of ideology is cyclical and thrives off of ignorance. It should be apparent to us all that we cannot wait for some other race to come and save us. We must save ourselves! I am well aware that many of you are probably furious by now  and are thinking  what right do I have to express the opinions I have thus far  as well as those I have al  luded too.  I have chosen to chronicle my experiences because of the diversity and seriousness of their content. There is far too much negativity thriving within our culture. There must be acknowledgment and accountability for the truth  whether good or bad. I am aware that not all of "us" have succumbed to the crippling mentality that is rampant in our community  and I have chosen to concentrate on individuals who have had a profound impact on my life. Any similarities and generalizations I illustrate are directed solely toward individuals in the black community who share the collective negative thinking and behavior that will hereafter be identified.  Additionally  throughout this book I will refer to African?Americans in four different ways; the first being "African?Americans"  denoting our status as citizens in the United States; secondly  as "Black"  a reference that identifies and defines our differences and struggles in this country; third  as "Niggas " a term which is often misunderstood and should not be confused with "Nigger". The term "nigga" has become an accepted form of reference among young black males used to express friendship (hence the term "My Nigga") as well as a blanket reference when speaking to  of  or about other black males in a non?personal manner. I felt it necessary to make this distinction because many of the experiences I will refer to mandate the use of the term to effectively communicate the attitude and mood that existed during the time each story took place; and fourth  as "Ghetto"  this term is largely intended as an internal reference commonly understood by blacks as a means to define the   less polished members of our community.  It is important to note that the use of either term has no negative connotation and is therefore not to be associated with any feeling as such.  My commentary is based on real?life situations  both good and bad  and how one African?American man was affected by them. To that end  I feel it is necessary to acknowledge that my intention is not to condemn the individuals I have encountered. Despite the negativity they have displayed  I only want to make them aware that the selfish and self debasing attitudes they subscribed to  in many ways  has caused them to become their own worst enemy. In the case of the black female's negative and limited perspective toward black men  the world  and subconsciously themselves  I submit that this mentality is perhaps single?handedly responsible for the lack of success  happiness  and quality of life that is at the center of every African?American woman's fantasy quest. It is also important to note that the selfish and negative attitudes at the core of the tension that exists between black women and men  has been deliberately created by "White America". For example  much of the existing resentment between black women and men can be traced as far back as slavery on up to present day. Many past issues have taken on new identities and have re?emerged in the form of corporate acceptance of black women and the corporate exclusion of black men. The resulting economic independence that some black women now enjoy has caused them to challenge and judge the black man for his absence within corporate America  without realizing and ackno  wledging that this absence is by design.  There are other "core" issues that have been passed down and nurtured from generation to generation  such as color barriers  light skin versus dark skin  good hair versus bad hair  loyalty  devotion  and economic status. Believe it or not  there was once a time when black women refused to date a black man if he didn't sell drugs or was not "thugged out". (a term for being rough or hoodlum-like) The reasoning behind it being that the "thug " and "drug dealer" lifestyle was synonymous with financial independence.  These issues  among others  relate directly to the confused mentality that exists within our internal society. Sadly that "confused mentality" is responsible for much of the neglect the African American "ghetto" community receives at the hands of our more affluent brethren. Who have locked it away in the basement  and seems to be more concerned with convincing the rest of the world that "ghetto America does not exist. Furthermore  the lack of acknowledgement of which I speak should not be confused with the impoverished masses of the African American community.  Their plight is a well-known reality  but in many cases much of ghetto America falls under that same umbrella. Be advised: this book is not a colorful or lighthearted look into "Black America".  Rather it should be viewed as a legitimate tool for identifying and changing the backward thinking that so many young African Americans (including myself) have come to perpetuate. Moreover  that "backward thinking" is the main   cause of our inability to strive for a common goal. An outcome that must be met; and can only be met  with Godly faith  positive strategy  cooperation  love  loyalty  self and mutual respect. *************************************************************  To read More go to www.blackrealitypublishing.com   To Unsubscribe: send mail to majordomo@FreeBSD.org with "unsubscribe freebsd-ports" in the body of the message
