Date: Wed Sep 11 03:25:27 2002 Return Path: Received: from lbrout13.listbuilder.com (lbrout13.listbuilder.com [204.71.191.17]) by lerami.lerctr.org (8.12.2/8.12.2/ 20020902 /$Revision: USD 1.30) with SMTP ID g8B8POE9005100 for ; Wed Sep 11 2002 03:25:25 -0500 (CDT) Received: (qmail 16858 triggered by uid 0); Sep 11, 2002 08:33:28 -0000 Date: Sep 11, 2002 08:33:28 -0000 Message ID: To: List Member Reply to: FIAZ-feedback-5@lb.bcentral.com From: 'ContraComm International Subject: SPS waived the rights to Slobodan Milosevic. MIME version: 1.0. Content type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii X-Virus Scanned: by amavisd-milter (http://amavis.org/) Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit g8B8POE9005100 Status: RO X-Status: X-Keywords: X-UID: 13 The Socialist Party of Serbia led by a group of old socialists led by Milomir Mini finally renounced the politics and heroic attitude of the party's chairman, Slobodan Milosevic, announcing that a poorly informed man, especially not from a cell, cannot lead such a large party as the Socialist Party Serbia, so his name was also Slobodan Milosevic.        Socialists, who today say that they are no longer idolaters of Slobodan Milosevic, while remaining in constant contact with members and sympathizers of this party, are trying to separate the defense of Slobodan Milosevic in The Hague from political life in Serbia, attributing to Milosevic's defenders from the National Committee for the release of S. Milosevic the goal freedom is to destroy the Socialist Party of Serbia.         Although, due to the same views, at one time the most polar socialist after the president of this party, prof. Branislav Ivkovic was expelled from the SPS ranks, and today the SPS leadership uses increasingly strict qualifications at the expense of its president, without fear that any of them may be expelled from the party.         In recent days, it is not uncommon for the party leadership to hear that Slobodan Milosevic is not the party and that he does not represent the party, but that the party is the leadership and management board of this party.         However, not everything is going according to the management's plans among the party's members and supporters.         Estimates even say that Bata Zivojinovic will win only 1% of the votes in the September elections.  Most party members still believe in their hero, Slobodan Milosevic.         According to party members, currently those in the party leadership who in recent years disinformed the party's president are trying to save themselves by eliminating president Slobodan Milosevic when they realized that they had made the call.         Young socialists, of which there are not many, as SPS once boasted, seem to be on the side of the party's chairman. Thus, during performances before municipal boards, you can hear convincing speeches by Dejan Stjepanovic and Igor Raicevic, as well as some of Milinka Isakovi from the ranks of young socialists, members of the organizational and political committee of the SPS president.          The speeches of these young people among party members are even ten times more important than the speeches of professional politicians who carry the burden of the past behind them.          The position of the Young Socialists' leadership differs from the position of the youth council, which also sides with the president.           Branko Ruzic and Dejan Backovic, once the greatest defenders and representatives of Slobodan Milosevic's character and actions, have today become his greatest critics. They are trying in every possible way to marginalize the group of young people who support him.          Even in recent days, it has been heard that the best recipe for maintaining leadership among young people is to connect family ties, which is why the chairwoman of the Young Socialists of Belgrade, Ana Djurovic, married Branko Ruzi, the chairman of the Young Socialists of Serbia, who took Dejn Backov, her vice-president, as her godfather. . Currently, Backovic is getting married to a young socialist who is a member of the youth council, and at the same time the sister of one of the IO GO SPS members is taking on another young socialist from the youth council as her godfather. To summarize, the young people in SPS behave like Italian mafia families in the 1960s in the USA.           The question is what will happen at the end of this story, but members and supporters will judge the performance of their leaders in the presidential election.           We just wonder what they will do if Bata is worse than Seselj, who was supported by President Slobodan Milosevic as a presidential candidate?        ________________________________________________________ Powered by List Builder To unsubscribe, click the link: http://lb.bcentral.com/ex/sp?c=15279&s=54EE057E0B6864FB&m=5

MIME Version: 1.0 Content Type: Text/Plain;charset="iso-8859-1" Content Transfer Encoding: 7-bit From: owner-freebsd-ports@FreeBSD.ORG List-ID: List-Archive: (Web Archive) List-Help: (List Instructions) List-Subscribe: List-Unsubscribe: X-Loop: FreeBSD.org Priority: Bulk Virus Scanned X: by amavisd-milter (http://amavis.org/) Status: RO X-Status: X-Keywords: X-UID: 22 My name is Jeremy Lessaris. I am looking for investment properties in the Midwest. The problem I have is that not everyone has experience with the properties I am looking for. You know which houses are almost certain to not sell; maybe they're really ugly, or they need a lot of work, or they live in a bad neighborhood. But for some reason, houses just aren't selling.  I need these homes... Most agents I've dealt with have been hesitant because the time and effort invested doesn't give much of a return. However, the private investors I work with use "unconventional" private financing, which allows us both to avoid long-term loan approvals. Most of the time we just pay cash and close within a week. I am pre-qualified by Greentree Funding for a $900,000 purchase mortgage loan based on a non-owner occupied loan at 90% LTV.  (And of course you will receive your full commission.) I am not a licensed real estate agent nor am I affiliated with any real estate company, which means I am free to work with you in any way I want. Don't get the impression that you have to pay below market value to be interested. Sometimes I even manage to pay the retail price. The only guarantee I give is that I will not waste your time and in most cases I can tell you over the phone whether I am interested or not.   If you are interested in purchasing a design home from our inventory or would like information about forming an alliance with Synteligent Properties, please contact me at @ 847.366.4300 or email me at @ jeremy@synteligent.com Best wishes Jeremy Lessaris 847.366.4300 www .intelligent. com jeremy@synteligent.com To unsubscribe: send an email to majordomo@FreeBSD.org with "unsubscribe freebsd-ports" in the body of the message

Date: Tue 17 Sep 2002 15:30:45 +0100 Reply to: "KOL. MICHAEL BUNDU Subject: [ILUG] HELP From: ilug-admin@linux.ie Errors To: ilug-admin@linux.ie X -Mailman-Version: 1.1 Precedence: Bulk List ID: Irish Linux User Group X-Beenthere: ilug @linux.ie Content transfer encoding: 8bit FROM: COL. MICHAEL BUNDU.  DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF CONGO.  Tel. No.: Your country Intl. access code +8821652098236 e-mail: mikebundu@rediffmail.com Dear Sir/Madam, I AM ASKING FOR IMMEDIATE HELP.   Please allow me to get to know you in this informal way. This is necessary due to my urgent need to find a reliable and trustworthy foreign partner. This request may seem strange and unwanted, but I seek your understanding and pray that you will take it seriously. My name is KOL. MICHAEL BUNDU of the Democratic Republic of the Congo and one of the close associates of former President of the Democratic Republic of the Congo LAURENT KABILA, of blessed memory, may his soul rest in peace.   Due to LAURENT KABILA'S military campaign to expel the rebels in my country, I and some of my colleagues were ordered by the late President Kabila to go abroad to purchase weapons and ammunition worth only twenty million five hundred thousand US dollars (US$20 ). 500,000.00) to fight the rebel group. We then received this money privately from then-President LAURENT KABILA, without the knowledge of other cabinet members. But when President Kabila was killed in a bloody shootout by one of his bodyguards the day before he was scheduled to leave Congo, we immediately decided to transfer the funds to a private security company here in Congo for safekeeping. The security of this amount is currently at risk due to the arrest and seizure of the property of Col. Rasheidi Karesava (one of Laurent Kabila's aides), a tribesman and other military personnel from our tribe by the new President of the Democratic Party of the Republic of Congo, son of the late President Laurent Kabila Joseph Kabila.   Therefore, we need a reliable and trustworthy foreign partner who will help us transfer this money from my country as the beneficiary.  We have enough "CONTACTS" here to transfer the fund under diplomatic cover to a security company in Europe on your behalf. This is to ensure that diplomatic baggage will be marked "CONFIDENTIAL" and will not pass normal customs/airport inspection.   Our inability to get this money out of the Congo all this time is due to a lack of trust in our supposed good friends (Western countries) who suddenly became hostile to those of us who worked with the late President Kabila immediately after his son took office . Although we have not seen or met each other, the information we have gathered from the associate working in your country has encouraged us and convinced us that with your sincere help, this transaction will be handled properly, with modesty and honesty, and will be a huge success within two weeks . This money is a state fund and therefore requires complete confidentiality.   We ask you to act on our behalf as a beneficiary of this fund in Europe. This is because we have limited ability to move and observe, so we want to be especially careful not to lose the fund we have worked so hard to earn. So if you want to help us move this fund out of Congo, you can contact me via my email addresses. Telephone/fax numbers. above, providing your telephone fax number and personal details so that we can discuss the terms and the amount of your share (in percentage) in helping us.  Please note that there is NO RISK associated with this Agreement as everyone's safety is guaranteed if we follow the required guidelines. I will therefore provide you with further details of this Agreement as soon as I am satisfied that you are interested in assisting us.   I must take this opportunity and means to beg you for your utmost leniency and to keep this matter extremely secret, regardless of your decision, while awaiting your prompt response. Thank you and God bless you.  Best regards, KOL. MICHAEL BUNDU (RTD). m_bundu@rediffmail.com N\B. When you call my line, you dial your country's international number. access code which you then dial directly, do not enter my country code, i.e. (243). Just dial your country's international number. access code + 88216 52098236. You can also contact me via the above email addresses.        -- Irish Linux Users Group: ilug@linux.ie http://www.linux.ie/mailman/listinfo/ilug for information about (un)subscriptions. An amount of 48 million dollars (forty-eight million United States) was deposited with a security company here in the country by the late Head of State (GEN.SANI ABACHA) for safekeeping. This money was deposited in secure vaults/boxes and marked as personal effects, so the security company does not know the true contents of the boxes. The money was originally intended to be used for his political campaign.  Since I was his family representative, he confided in me the relevant documents regarding this deposit before he died of cardiac arrest.  In fact, we have made arrangements with the foreign security company to transfer this money via diplomatic shipment to its offshore branch, where you will be required to claim the shipment as the true beneficiary of the shipment. You should know that this business is safe and 100% risk-free as it does not involve drug money or terrorist funds. Please also send me phone and fax numbers to facilitate communication. When you express your desire to me by sending the above requirement. The transaction will be completed within 7 (seven) business days.  I will be waiting for your urgent reply. Sep 26, 2002 04:22:43 +0200 Subject: BUSINESS COOPERATION (URGENT/CONFIDENTIAL) X-Mailer: Microsoft Outlook Express 5.00.2919.6900 DM MIME version: 1.0 Content type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"  Dear Sir, My name is Vincent Nnaji Bank, Manager of Standard Trust Bank Lagos Nigeria. I have an urgent and very confidential business proposition for you.  On January 6, 1998, a foreign petroleum consultant, a foreign contractor from the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation, Mr. James Herbert, placed a numbered twelve-calendar-month fixed deposit with my branch in the amount of US$20 million (twenty million US dollars). After reaching maturity, I sent a routine notification to his mailing address but received no response. After a month, we sent a reminder and finally learned from his contract employers, the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation, that Mr. James Herbert had died in a car accident.  Upon further investigation, I learned that he had died intestate and all attempts to trace his next of kin had been unsuccessful. I therefore made further inquiries and discovered that Mr. James Herbert had not named any next of kin or relatives in all of his official documents, including his bank deposit documents with my bank. This sum of $20 million was carefully transferred from my bank to the security company for safekeeping. No one will ever come forward to claim it.  Under Nigerian law, after 5 years, the money will revert to the ownership of the Nigerian government if no one files a claim for the funds. Therefore, my proposal is that I would like you, as a foreigner, to be the owner of the money that I deposited with the security company in two luggage boxes, although the security company does not know the contents of the boxes because I have marked them with photographic materials for export. I am writing to you, because as a government official I cannot maintain an offshore account or have an account worth more than $1 million.  I want to introduce you as the owner of the boxes in a security company so that you can collect them with the help of my lawyer. All this to ensure that the fruits of this old man's labor do not fall into the hands of corrupt government officials.  It's simple. Please provide your full names and address immediately so that the Attorney can prepare the necessary documents that will make you the owner of the boxes. The money will be divided 70% for me and 25% for you, and 5% will cover all expenses.  There is no risk because all formalities related to this transaction will be handled by the Representative, which will guarantee the successful implementation of this transaction. If you are interested, please reply immediately to my private e-mail address.  Once I receive your response, I will provide more details and relevant documents to help you understand the transaction. Please maintain the utmost confidentiality and be assured that this transaction will be most beneficial for both of us as I will need your help to invest my share in your country.  I am waiting for your urgent reply via my private email to express your interest.  Thank you and best regards, MR VINCENT NNAJI.
